    {
      "id": 358429,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>The proton NMR spectrum of a compound with the formula C<sub>5</sub>H<sub>10</sub>O is shown. The normal carbon-13 and the DEPT experimental results are tabulated. The infrared spectrum shows a broad peak at about 3340 cm<sup>–1</sup> and a medium-sized peak at about 1651 cm<sup>–1</sup>. Draw the structure of this compound.</p>\n<table class=\"unnumbered\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th><b>Normal Carbon</b></th>\n<th><b>DEPT-135</b></th>\n<th><b>DEPT-90</b></th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>    22.2 ppm</td>\n<td>Positive</td>\n<td>No peak</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td> 40.9</td>\n<td>Negative</td>\n<td>No peak</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td> 60.2</td>\n<td>Negative</td>\n<td>No peak</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>112.5</td>\n<td>Negative</td>\n<td>No peak</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>142.3</td>\n<td>No peak</td>\n<td>No peak</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<img src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBbjBVIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--2944627cf8807329d0c44bb6a3f2275715dfc39f/OChem_13_EC_030.jpg\" alt=\"Proton spectrum of C 5 H 10 O shifts: 1.75 (singlet), 2.15 (singlet), 2.3 (triplet), 3.7 (triplet), and 4.8 (doublet). Relative areas of 3, 1.2, 2, 2.1, and 2.1 respectively.\">",
